text: Helonastes acentrus is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Ian Francis Bell Common in 1960. It is found in Australia, where it has been recorded from Queensland. The larvae possibly feed on Eleocharis species.A revision of the Australian Stem Borers hitherto referred to Schoenobius and Scirpophaga (Lepidoptera: Pyralidae, Schoenobiinae) ==References== Category:Moths described in 1960 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Helonastes acentrus
